reviews.text:
More little children than animals. Pay for parking on honor system. Fog. Farm and stuffed animals in the gift shop $$, no free bag for your purchase. Most people indoors. The little ones (like 2 years old) seem to be the most inquisitive. I had a good sandwich. I enjoyed watching the snow monkeys and the penguins.
 You can't sit down and really study the animals, it's kinda like stop for a couple minutes and move along or shuffle by. Lots of young parents enjoying their young children. We use to ride our dirt bikes (motorcycles) on this vast property. We were riding here on the ground breaking day, but missed seeing the governor. Lots to see, but close every day at 4 pm. That's sad.

Fun to go with family and friends.  Lots of walking.  They have scooters if needed for family members that aren't able to walk distances.  Can be high dollars if you get gifts and food.  Can bring food in to eat. Plan on being there for a half a day at least. Or longer if needed.  They also offer special events  to go to.  Always nice to see the zoo.
I love this zoo. It's large enough for a full day of fun. The cafe is a great spot to stop and have lunch with many options. The only reason I'm not giving 5 stars is the price is a little high.

I had a good time at the zoo when visiting Minnesota. Saw many animals that I can not see in my home country and am looking forward to going back this year. Although there were many young kids  when we were leaving if you get there nice and early there are few small children. Over all amazing zoo.

The MN Zoo has held a special place in our family's life for nearly 25 years, not just when our children were young, but even now when they're grown and gone. The exhibits are diverse, constantly improving, and thoughtfully arranged. There are no cages; barriers blend into the exhibit, making you feel like you're part of the animal's environment, not forcing them into yours. The result is a warm, welcoming, and thoroughly enjoyable experience that keeps us coming back year after year. It's expensive for a single trip, but you'd be missing a lifetime of memories with your children if you only came once; twice pays for an annual membership.

Love this place for their holiday setting.  We have gone every year for the last 5 years.  Just a great way to get into the holiday season.  If you like to see and hear some local history, it is a great way to spend an afternoon.  And volunteers set up Christmas lights for December, that are on every night.  Great place to grab some pictures.
Our family loves this place.
1st grade field trip, so educational

This is a great place to come and explore things of the past in the turn of the century village. No matter what your age you will find something to peak your interest. Enjoy singing Christmas carols in the church.  Watch the blacksmith, print maker, or the cabinet maker as they work their trade. Go visit the barbershop and catch up on the latest. Feel free to ask all the questions you want as they're happy to teach you about their work. And be sure to go visit the lovely homes in the village and watch as they prepare for and entertain guests for Christmas.
Such a fun, unique place! Our whole family loves to go!
My wife daughter and I visited for breakfast. Service was very prompt and attentive. The staff was super friendly. My 5 year old loved the pictures of James Dean and Marilyn Monroe.

Food tasted good but waitress had issues with the order I asked for a Greek breakfast and got the gyro omelette. Not what I wanted but chose not to send it back. We had two kids in our party the kitchen sent out 2 orders of Mickey mouse pancakes that were not ordered. One person was never asked what they wanted. The waitress asked questions but did not wait to hear the full answers more than once. I have been to this place many times but have never had such poor service.

Great fries... decent breakfast... fun ice cream flavors. This is a great neighborhood diner. We love walking over in the summer for a treat. Comfortable seating too and a little space with toys in back for kiddos... which helps when grown ups need to talk.
Burger was on point very tasty and juicy. And they have the best fries I've ever had. Best kept secret.  Great staff and positive attitudes.

Was impressed with the menu size. Pancakes, eggs, waffles and hash browns were all very good. Was not impressed with the chicken fried steak and mozzarella sticks. The coating for bothering were too hard and the marinara sauce was cold. Our server was very nice.

Food was tasty and prepared correctly and fast. Three stars though because the staff really wasn't very professional and the store was trashy. I would have given leeway due to the hour of day and number of customers. But when you look over the whole restaurant and realize there isn't one single clean table and you will have to clean your own to sit down.... Come on! Floors were gross, booths gross, and staff are chatting with their work friends but no one wants to clean the shop. Just gross...

Good chicken fingers, but a word of warning - that's all they have. Chicken fingers, fries, toast, and one sauce. I am not a fan of mayo based sauces (which I believe theirs was), so I had no other sauce option. Theirs fries are average, toast and chicken fingers were above average, though not the best I've had. Overall, I wouldn't hesitate to go back, but I also wouldn't select it myself.

I hate chicken fingers, absolutely HATE chicken fingers. But at Raising Canes, it's totally different!  The chicken is always on point. Fresh never frozen! 

I could eat here weekly.  If you haven't tried this place you are missing out! 

I get the Box Combo and substitute the coleslaw for extra fries.  Their canes sauce is amazing! Dip that chicken right into the sauce. Getting hungry writing this. 

This place can speak for itself, just look how it is always busy. But don't fear, it's always worth the wait!

Never been here before, but the food was good n the staff was friendly. The drive through was busy but I went inside and it was really quick. All chicken fingers and sides as the name suggests. The sweet tea was really good. Considering I just got back from NC it was good to get some just like they make it everywhere there.

This restaurant has incredible chicken and food in general. The staff is friendly and helpful. However the restaurant is constantly busy and often most of the seating is full. This leads to longer wait times for food than I would like. In addition, the restaurants seating is not very clean. It doesn't seem like they ever wipe down the tables or chairs during the day. Everything seems a little greasy. Overall, the food is still worth return trips, but the rest of the restaurant lacks.

First time here, and most likely will not be back. Food was good however service was lacking. Wait staff was inattentive and never looked past the table he was at to see if others needed assistance. The ground beef has a nearly equal portion of peppers in it, something that is not expected. I love peppers, but not that much! Worth a visit for sure, but not my favorite place to go by any means.

Probably one of the best options for Mexican food in Apple Valley if not the best. Their table side guacamole is excellent and the prices are more than reasonable for what you get. They have also proven themselves very attentive and helpful when we dined there with a larger group. There are cheaper options probably for Mexican fair but you get what you pay for. They also have coupons in the paper fairly often and the fajitas for two is an excellent money saver and honestly is enough food for three or even four people.

We stopped in for a late lunch as this is one of our favorite restaurants. Service is always good but this time we were lucky enough to get Elias D as our waiter. He has to be one of the kindest and most efficient waiters. He had our chips and salsas to the table before we had even settled in. His knowledge of the menu was outstanding and not to mention the guacamole he made for us at our table was awesome. Thanks Elias D for the very enjoyable experience. :)

Decor is lovely! Service was quick and very courteous even during peek hrs on Friday night. The food was fine but I had been hoping for an authentic Mexican place. Here they served ranch along w their mild salsa to go with the (excellent) chips and “nacho cheese sauce” over the chimichangas. Just wasn’t what I had been looking for.

Not sure what happened to this place. Last two times we were here the service has been incredibly slow. Took over 30 minutes to get our food when it wasn't even busy. Food is good but comes out cold. The woman who sat us threw the menus on the table, she also happened to be our waitress. After that it took her approximately 10 minutes to come back to get our drink order. We come here often, but after these last few visits, I'm not sure we will be back.

Like kallies blend. Their popcorn is great flavor, caramel is crunchy and delicious with nice buttery flavor. Cheese is good, salty and has a good mouth feel smooth and cheesy. butter not overly flavor makes for a great balance. Staff is good, receptive and friendly. They also have ice cream. never had it but wanted to note it's present.

We ordered 15 gallons each of buttery white, caramel and white cheddar for my daughters wedding.  They had it all ready when I came to pick up, helped me carry it to my car and even gave me extra empty bags to use when I asked!  We got so many great compliments about how great the popcorn tasted and wanted to know where we got it from!! Thank you Kalli’s!

I have enjoyed butter and salted popcorn from Kalli's for a few years now.  It's great you can get the butter and salt level customized to your preference and the price is on par or better than other shops.
Great gourmet popcorn. Great staff. Great management. Clean & friendly environment. The popcorn really is good.
Lots of choices!!! Friendly staff, affordable prices

Great food, good service, and its pretty quick. The only issue is they closed shop for a whole month once and left no indication anywhere on the web or even on their answering machine to give you a heads up. I don't exactly live close to this place, but I was happy to drive out there expecting food. That's poor business etiquette and very inconsiderate to faithful customers.

I'm speechless, both from a mouthful of delicious food and so much to say about our experience! First time eating here tonight, walked in and we were warmly greeting by the family. Corrine asked us what we like then made perfect recommendations. She heard my wife mention it was my birthday and she wished me a happy birthday. I tried their coffee and it was incredible. Then as we dove into it meals the owners son David brought out their signature Golden Milky Bun as a birthday treat on the house, wow. Then Corrine came out to chat for a while. They just created more loyal customers.

Great Malaysian food restaurant.  The restaurant is smaller as most people do takeout.  A lot of people were coming in to get their buns as well.  Mee goreng was definitely my favorite! Would recommend friends to come.

Owners are very nice, friendly and great service. The pastries are very good and it's very hard to find one of a kind baked goodies. The red bean paste buns are my favorite and the one with the cream. Otherwise everything is very good in taste and it will be worth your money!

What's not to like about Satay 2 Go?

I love all of the pastries and buns that they have to offer. My favorite is the red bean bun.

This place is worth the drive. The food was amazing and the service was great. The menu is extensive. Everyone loved their dishes and we got a variety. I love Thai food and use the universal and well loved dish of Pad Thai as my litmus test for Thai restaurants. Not many Thai restaurants pass my test (too dry, too sweet, not sweet enough, etc.). Taste of Thaiyai passed with flying colors! We will be back!

Wow!! I've been here before and Taste of Thaiyai never disappoints and this time was no exception, I was in food heaven!! 
I got the spicy crab legs and they were SO juicy and tender, I couldn't believe the portion! A huge crab claw, multiple legs and knuckles with tons of veggies in a very flavorful sauce. Service was so quick! We had our appetizer out within minutes of sitting down and our entrees shortly after. We were in and out within 30 - 35 min, tops, and the place was slammed! 
This place is doing Thai food right!

This is a very good restaurant for Thai food. 
The ambience is good. Everyone here was very friendly and accomdating. They took the order with smile and bought us the food with a smile and also checked upon how was the food

After placing the order the food arrived soon and hot. The food was very good and fresh. 

There is plenty of parking available here.this is little hidden and gem of a place in the shopping center in the Apple valley area. I don't remember the shopping center name but this is besides a bar and a grill. 

The pricing is very inexpensive. The Thai tea was very good and very inexpensive compared to other Thai places.

This is straight up my favorite restaurant in the city. I have many friends and coworkers that agree. We just absolutely love the food here. Huge menu has a little something for everyone. The spring rolls are authentic, delicious, and EXTRA THICC.

Service for dine in can feel a little overbearing though? Waiters try too hard which can sometimes feel like you're being stared daggers. Don't need to top off my water every time I take a sip! Too much of a good thing I suppose.

(Takeout) Wow, this was great. Papaya salad was incredible. Other apps and entrees were delicious as well. The staff was SO FRIENDLY when I went in to pick up the food. They were clearly slammed with takeout orders, but mine was ready on time with a great big smile on their faces.
Great staff and great meats! They have amazing jerky bites! a bit pricy but well worth it!

Been a customer for 30 years. Quality is slipping a lot. Brats tasted slightly rancid this summer tried them twice. Went to get steaks today, a Saturday.  Grill steaks weren't even red, grainy and pinkish. Sirloin was NOT fresh. I posted a review on FB too, only because I want the quality we used to get! Also need to get with the times and offer grass fed, free range options. The chicken is clearly from chickens pumped with hormones.

I usually love this place that being said I buy a lot of regular beef jerky and it's not cheap but very worth it.  Well last time I went in and got a $20 bag I was very bummed to find out that they gave me peppered instead of regular.  So my family and I scraped all the pepper off of it that we could and tried to choke it down.  The next time I went in to buy a bag I let them know what happened and they told me they couldn't do anything about it because I didn't bring in the beef jerky. It was a real bummer.
Staff was really nice and helpful. Food amazing as always.
A place where you can get market beef, pork, chicken , etc and trimmings to compliment a meal. Staff helpful.

We stopped in for the all you can eat sushi after being told by a reliable source to try it. It was nothing to write home about. The restaurant was pretty dead, unlike the other sushi places I have tried around dinner time. The server acted like he didn't want to be there and tried to make some weird jokes that just made interacting with him awkward. Most of the crab options used imitation crab and a lot of the other rolls ALL had salmon (I'm not a fan). There is also a note stating there are no substitutions or modifications to the menu. Everyone at the table must order the all you can eat, other restaurants don't have this policy. We were also charged an extra 15%, the menu states "Food waste is an additional 15% charge and cannot	order	anymore". We had no food waste, we ate all of our sushi! I get better quality and better service at my other sushi place, I won't be back.

Food was not the best. Service was horrible. Our waitress was extremely condescending. We ordered two items that never arrived and she wanted to argue that we never ordered them when all four of us KNEW that we did. When my friend asked for shrimp sauce she refused to give us any because it wasn't included in the all you can eat menu she said...even though she offered to pay for it. It's a condiment for crying out loud! At the end of our meal she said "if you want anything else let me know...NOW." We all looked at each other and shook our heads. We won't be back. As others said, their roles are a little weird. They make you all do all you can eat or not, you can't mix, they won't bring you more food till you finish, etc

This is by far the worst sushi I have ever had. The fish was very different than what I've had elsewhere for the last 15 years. It was absolutely nasty. I gagged trying to eat some of it to avoid the 15% food waste penalty which they tell you right away (must be a pattern).   

Each sushi piece was almost all rice too, so you'd have to eat pounds of rice to get a bit of fish. If you order sashimi you'll throw up from the fish's texture, smell or taste.  

The food is way overpriced. Don't be fooled by the buffet.  I do NOT recommend anyone visit this place.   

Nasty is the word to describe my experience and the only way I'd go back is if someone paid me an hourly rate to sit around and watch them eat.  

AVOID THIS PLACE LIKE THE BLACK PLAGUE!!!

There has ton of food can eat. Best quality service ever. I loved the funny hibachi chef and the polite sever. of course the Delicious yummy food。 I will go over again and again!!!    lets eat in Osaka people!!!!!!!!!!!
This isn't a perfect place for all you can eat but it's great for finer taste compared to some other Japanese restaurant.  Great theme and funny servers. Would come again.
